title: Warrior's Way
author: Exodia
pages:
#- If you have not read§0
§0part 1, §4Warrior's §4Tomb§0,§0
§0please do so. Although§0
§0this book can be§0
§0completed on its own,§0
§0the events of the first§0
§0book tie into this§0
§0adventure. Enjoy part§0
§02!§0
§0
§0DemonicOctopus, aka§0
§0GreatLordOz§0

#- You put on your new§0
§0treasure and look§0
§0behind you to see the§0
§0man that was in the§0
§0mirror. "No one leaves§0
§0this place," he§0
§0chuckles. He walks up§0
§0to you and attempts to§0
§0lunge his hand into§0
§0your heart but stops§0
§0inches away. "On§0
§0second thought..."§0
§0(Go to page 3)
#- I couldn't kill you with§0
§0that amulet of§0
§0protection on.§0
§0However, you cannot§0
§0leave this place§0
§0without my guidance. Do§0
§0you give the man your§0
§0amulet in exchange for§0
§0information (Page 8)§0
§0or attempt to find a§0
§0way out on your own§0
§0(Page 32)§0

#- You throw the sloth§0
§0off of your shoulder§0
§0in disgust. You don't§0
§0have time for pets.§0
§0The slime girl looks at§0
§0you with flames in her§0
§0eyes. But they weren't§0
§0just in her §0eyes...She§0
§0set you on fire! "How§0
§0dare you hurt my pet."§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You lean in closer and§0
§0the slime girl gives you§0
§0a kiss. You instantly§0
§0black out and wake up§0
§0chained to the wall.§0
§0The slime girl is§0
§0standing in front of§0
§0you and smiles. "Do§0
§0you want to do this the§0
§0easy way (Page 13) or§0
§0the hard way (Page§0
§039).§0

#- You reach down and§0
§0feel a tentacle with§0
§0suction cups. The§0
§0tentacle slowly lights§0
§0up and releases a§0
§0powerful electric§0
§0charge, frying your§0
§0brain completely. Next§0
§0time, don't grab a§0
§0shocktopus.§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- The sloth rushes over§0
§0to you and decapitates§0
§0Lucifier in one blow.§0
§6§lYou did §6§lit! §0Lucifer is§0
§0dead! But where is the§0
§0way out? At that§0
§0moment a portal§0
§0appears at your feet.§0
§0Can you finally leave§0
§0this tomb?§0
§0
§5§l...To§5§l be continued.§0

#- You hand the man the§0
§0amulet and feel a§0
§0sense of warmth rush§0
§0over you. You're on§0
§0fire! The man chuckles§0
§0again. "I am Lucifer,§0
§0the keeper of this§0
§0tomb. There is no§0
§0escape you fool."§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You start to climb§0
§0down the vines but§0
§0they snap instantly§0
§0under your weight. You§0
§0try to kick off the§0
§0ledge in an attempt to§0
§0reach the hay stack§0
§0but fall head first to§0
§0the floor below. Your§0
§0neck snaps instantly.§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You unchain the dog§0
§0but as you suspected,§0
§0it was already dead.§0
§0You proceed to the§0
§0next room and see a§0
§0swarm of hornets§0
§0flying toward you. Do§0
§0you retreat to the§0
§0previous room (Page§0
§020), try to run past§0
§0the hornets (Page 25)§0
§0or prepare to attack§0
§0(Page 48)§0

#- You fling off your§0
§0clothes before you§0
§0get burned.§0
§0Unfortunately your§0
§0amulet got destroyed§0
§0in the process. The§0
§0man from the mirror§0
§0materializes before§0
§0you. "I've been waiting§0
§0for this moment." Do§0
§0you fight him (Page§0
§016) or attempt to flee§0
§0(Page 45).§0

#- You accept the time§0
§0stone and notice§0
§0strange markings all§0
§0over it. The old man§0
§0informs you that you§0
§0can travel to the§0
§0future (Page 31) or§0
§0return to the past to§0
§0rethink the decisions§0
§0you have made (Page§0
§043).§0

#- The easy way of§0
§0course! The slime girl§0
§0forces you to drink a§0
§0mysterious liquid and it§0
§0starts oozing out of§0
§0your pores. It is the§0
§0most intense pain you§0
§0have ever felt! You§0
§0scream in pain as your§0
§0heart stops.§0
§0
§4§lYou had died.§0

#- You open the door and§0
§0enter the dark room.§0
§0The door swings§0
§0closed behind you and§0
§0locks! The walls are§0
§0lined with spikes and§0
§0you notice them slowly§0
§0getting closer. You try§0
§0to escape but the§0
§0walls close, ending§0
§0your life.§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- The sword burrows§0
§0into the sand and your§0
§0ankle is released! You§0
§0try to pick up your§0
§0sword but it is lunged§0
§0into your chest by a§0
§0skeletal hand. "I'm§0
§0sorry sir. I am just a§0
§0sword and obey any§0
§0master."§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You can't run from§0
§0this man forever. "You§0
§0dare pick a fight with§0
§0Lucifer!" he roared.§0
§0He rushes at you and§0
§0you blast him with an§0
§0icicle spell. Lucifer§0
§0shrugs it off and§0
§0throws a punch§0
§0straight at your face.§0
§0You dodge but your§0
§0pet sloth (Page 30)§0

#- You enter the door§0
§0and see a Chimera in§0
§0front of you. It tries§0
§0to strike you with its§0
§0snake tail but you§0
§0knock it away. You§0
§0realize you are§0
§0outmatched. Do you try§0
§0to run away (Page 38)§0
§0or test your luck and§0
§0attack it (Page 35).§0

#- You head down the§0
§0spiral staircase and§0
§0see a dog chained to§0
§0broken post ahead of§0
§0you. The dog seems§0
§0lifeless and doesn't§0
§0move as you walk§0
§0toward it. Do you§0
§0unchain the dog (Page§0
§010) or move ahead§0
§0ignoring the poor§0
§0creature (Page 49)§0

#- You leave the drain§0
§0alone but a skeletal§0
§0hand grabs your ankle§0
§0from the sand! "Let me§0
§0get him sir!" your§0
§0sword insists. What§0
§0other choice do you§0
§0really have? Do you§0
§0attempt to flee (Page§0
§029) or let the sword§0
§0attack (Page 15).§0

#- You run back into the§0
§0previous room and§0
§0notice the dog isn't§0
§0there! You feel sharp§0
§0teeth sink into the§0
§0back of your neck as§0
§0you collapse onto§0
