§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You walk over to the§0
§0candlestick but the§0
§0ground underneath§0
§0you collapses! You fall§0
§0into a dark room with§0
§0shallow water. You feel§0
§0something slimy at§0
§0your ankles. Do you§0
§0try to grab the slimy§0
§0thing (Page 6) or try§0
§0to kick it off of you§0
§0(Page 44).§0

#- You pull the plug and§0
§0all of the sand is§0
§0drained from the room.§0
§0On the floor you see a§0
§0lifeless skeleton and§0
§0what appears to be a§0
§0coffin. Do you open§0
§0the coffin (Page 37)§0
§0or search the room§0
§0for another exit (Page§0
§042).§0

#- You pick up the chains§0
§0and shuffle into a side§0
§0room. An old man with a§0
§0cane greets you. "Oh§0
§0are you an escaped§0
§0prisoner? Let me help§0
§0you out with a free§0
§0item." Would you like§0
§0the time stone (Page§0
§012), a talking sword§0
§0(Page 50), or music§0
§0box (Page 27).§0

#- You pick up the staff§0
§0and feel magical§0
§0energy flow through§0
§0your body. You aim the§0
§0wand at the chimera§0
§0and blow it to pieces.§0
§0Your amulet seems to§0
§0react to the wand and§0
§0a secret door§0
§0materializes in front§0
§0of you. You step inside§0
§0(Page 33).§0

#- You attempt to rush§0
§0past the hornets but§0
§0there are too many of§0
§0them! You feel their§0
§0stingers pierce your§0
§0flesh and venom fill§0
§0your veins. You§0
§0struggle to breathe§0
§0as your throat swells§0
§0up.§0
§0
§4§lYou have died.§0

#- You take a few steps§0
§0back and lunge out the§0
§0window. You barely§0
§0reach the haypile and§0
§0you are somehow§0
§0unhurt! You look§0
§0around the room and§0
§0see two doors. Do you§0
